Hexenwail - Compiling from source
=================================

Hexenwail uses CMake and builds on Linux and Windows.
The recommended way to build on NixOS/Nix is with the provided flake.


Building with Nix (recommended):
================================

    nix build

This produces the binary in result/bin/.


Building with CMake:
====================

Prerequisites:
  - CMake 3.20+
  - A C compiler with C11 support (GCC 10+, Clang 12+)
  - SDL3 development libraries
  - OpenGL 4.3 capable driver

Optional libraries for music playback:
  - libogg and libvorbis (or libtremor) for OGG Vorbis
  - libmad or libmpg123 for MP3
  - libogg, opus, and opusfile for Opus
  - libFLAC for FLAC
  - libxmp or libmikmod for tracker music (MOD/S3M/XM/IT)

Build steps:

    mkdir build && cd build
    cmake ..
    make

The binary will be named glhexen2 (Linux) or glh2.exe (Windows).


Cross-compiling for Windows:
============================

Use MinGW-w64 with CMake:

    mkdir build-win && cd build-win
    cmake -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=../cmake/mingw-w64.cmake ..
    make


